The board shall issue invitations to join the council to no less than two (2) representatives of each of the following groups:
Family members of individuals with mental illness, alcohol and other drug abuse disorders, and dual diagnoses;
Consumers of mental health and substance abuse services;
County officials and business leaders;
Health departments and primary care physicians;
Advocates and community organizations;
Educators and school personnel;
Regional interagency councils established under KRS Chapter 200;
Law enforcement and court personnel;
Public and private organizations, agencies, or facilities that provide services for mental health and substance abuse in the region that represent inpatient services, outpatient services, residential services, and community-based supportive housing programs;
Individuals who provide mental health and substance abuse services in the region; and
Public and private hospitals that provide mental health and substance abuse services.
